that continue to exist, and continue to be shared.

00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.840
People think that it's outdated.

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:40.640
They think that when someone appears on a 
video, words pop up automatically underneath

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:48.160
as soon as someone clicks a button. They 
thought that subtitling is there for people

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:54.160
who do not have a computer with sound - you will 
be surprised how often that comes up as a reason!

00:09:56.800 --> 00:10:00.240
People also think that accessibility 
does not relate to video.

00:10:02.640 --> 00:10:07.200
And the one that we increasingly 
hear - it's for old people, or for

00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:11.680
people who really aren't our customers, so 
therefore we don't need to worry about it.

