00:17:27.520 --> 00:17:33.040
From an education and training perspective,
provision of visual representations

00:17:33.040 --> 00:17:38.800
of technical terms, jargon, and acronyms 
allow for the reinforcement of learning.

00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:43.280
The three key learning styles that 
I'm sure you've heard of elsewhere

00:17:43.840 --> 00:17:49.120
are visual, auditory, and kinetic. And you 
should hopefully see these now on screen.

00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:57.760
That basically means that people learn 
visually through seeing, auditory through

00:17:57.760 --> 00:18:06.000
hearing, and kinetic through doing. All of these 
styles of learning are better supported when

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:13.840
the visual picture and the audio commentary is 
reinforced with a visual underscoring of text.

00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:22.400
Even without the express intention of educating, 
provision of subtitles can even subliminally

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:27.840
help speakers of other languages acquire or 
appreciate subtleties of the original language.

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:34.320
Usage, slang, the idiomatic phrases 
we all use, spelling and much more.

00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:44.960
The automated transcription software service 
Sonix has found that 80 percent of all social

00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:51.200
