A statistic which might make you think that

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:59.440
doing that defeats the object of the medium. But 
be that as it may, it also poses an opportunity

00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:07.760
to reach that switch off audience more effectively 
by using subtitles. Being able to read information

00:19:07.760 --> 00:19:15.840
to absorb the content helps us to understand,
to respond, explore, and apply that knowledge.

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:25.280
Subtitles really do reinforce learning. I've 
worked in learning and CPD for nearly 20

00:19:25.280 --> 00:19:34.000
years or more now, and every time we have 
subtitles, I know the learners are learning

00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:37.840
more, they're accessing more, they're retaining 
it more, and they're being able to apply it.

00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:43.760
Subtitling can now be 
achieved increasingly quickly

00:19:44.560 --> 00:19:51.840
and economically through newer 
technology and online tools.

00:19:55.840 --> 00:20:02.080
Please try and keep that in your minds and 
